# Testing Conventions — IronLayer

## Test Layout

```
tests/
├── unit/                   # Fast, no I/O, no API calls
│   ├── test_planner.py
│   ├── test_graph.py
│   └── test_diff.py
├── integration/            # Real Databricks — skip without credentials
│   └── test_executor.py
└── conftest.py             # Shared fixtures
```

## Fixtures — Mock External Services in Unit Tests

```python
# conftest.py
from unittest.mock import Mock, patch
import pytest


@pytest.fixture
def mock_databricks():
    """Mock Databricks WorkspaceClient for unit tests."""
    with patch('core_engine.executor.WorkspaceClient') as mock_cls:
        client = Mock()
        client.sql.return_value = Mock(fetch_all=Mock(return_value=[]))
        mock_cls.return_value = client
        yield client
```

## Markers

```python
@pytest.mark.integration   # Requires real credentials
@pytest.mark.skipif(
    not os.getenv("DATABRICKS_TOKEN"),
    reason="DATABRICKS_TOKEN not set",
)
```

## Coverage Target

- **Unit tests:** 85%+ for `core_engine/` (deterministic code = highly testable)
- **Integration tests:** smoke-test happy paths for executor

## Running Tests

```bash
uv run pytest tests/unit/ -v --tb=short
uv run pytest tests/unit/ --cov=core_engine --cov-report=term-missing
uv run pytest tests/integration/ -v -m integration
```
